    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; 5 Engine Service Manual - Crankcase, Crankshaft, and Camshaft -
        Cleaning, Inspection and Testing - Camshaft Bushings
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s26508.2.5" svcproctype="measure" graphiccount="2">
        <title>Camshaft Bushings</title>
        <para>Inspect the four camshaft bushings for wear and proper running clearance as follows:</para>
        <figure id="f3000936" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ03/J03030.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Camshaft bushing measurement</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Using a
                <hotlnk document="eges390_351.xml" xrefid="t390001403">telescoping gauge</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="t390001403"/>, measure camshaft bushing inside diameter with bushings installed in
                crankcase.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3000937" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd06/D0620.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Measurement of telescoping gauge</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Outside micrometer</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Telescoping gauge</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Measure telescoping gauge with a 2-3 inch micrometer and record measurement.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To determine running clearance for each bushing and journal, subtract previous camshaft
                journal diameter reading from camshaft bushing inside diameter reading. See
                <hotlnk document="eges390_349.xml" xrefid="E30009A">Specifications
                    <xref refid="E30009A"/>
                </hotlnk>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If maximum allowable running clearance is exceeded, replace camshaft bushings. See camshaft
                bushing removal and installation procedures within this section. Also, see
                <hotlnk document="eges390_349.xml" xrefid="E30009A">Specifications
                    <xref refid="E30009A"/>
                </hotlnk>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect each bushing bore in crankcase for burrs or debris that could potentially damage new
                bushings.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove burrs and clean bores thoroughly before installing new camshaft bushings.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
